        },
        "subject": "LU-287 handle the glimpse callback race with lock cancel",
        "message": "LU-287 handle the glimpse callback race with lock cancel\n\n  If lock cancel and glimpse callback happened at the same time on\n  client, glimpse callback could read the shrinked kms(which is less\n  than actual size).\n  When such race happen, we should let the glmipse callback return\n  -EINVAL to inform server to update LVB from disk.\n\nIssue:\nSigned-off-by: Niu Yawei <niu@whamcloud.com>\nChange-Id: I32747cda570433913ec9ed8300e0ce24777c7f53\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/b1_8"
    }
